              <p>Cryo-EM maps/associated coordinates of atomic models have been deposited in the Electron Microscopy Data Bank/Protein Data Bank with the following accession codes: <a href="https://doi.org/10.2210/pdb6YSR/pdb">PDB 6YSR</a> and <a href="https://www.ebi.ac.uk/pdbe/entry/emdb/EMD-10905">EMD-10905</a> (Pâ+â9 stalled complex), <a href="https://doi.org/10.2210/pdb6YSS/pdb">PDB 6YSS</a> and <a href="https://www.ebi.ac.uk/pdbe/entry/emdb/EMD-10906">EMD-10906</a> (Pâ+â9 post-hydrolysis), <a href="https://doi.org/10.2210/pdb6YST/pdb">PDB 6YST</a> and <a href="https://www.ebi.ac.uk/pdbe/entry/emdb/EMD-10907">EMD-10907</a> (Pâ+â9 tRNA hybrid state), <a href="https://doi.org/10.2210/pdb6YSU/pdb">PDB 6YSU</a> and <a href="https://www.ebi.ac.uk/pdbe/entry/emdb/EMD-10908">EMD-10908</a> (Pâ+â0 post-hydrolysis). Cryo-EM micrographs and particle images have been deposited in the EMPIAR database (<a href="https://www.ebi.ac.uk/pdbe/emdb/empiar/">https://www.ebi.ac.uk/pdbe/emdb/empiar/</a>) with accession code EMPIAR-10443. Source data are provided with this paper.</p>
